Contrary to the other reviews, there was a crowd waiting at the door at noon. Despite this, we were seated promptly.   We initially chose this restaurant because of a coupon in the newspaper. We got 1/2 pound prime rib, a dozen shrimp and 2 sides (I chose the garden salad very crisp and garlic mash). The food was satisfactory, but wasn't worth any more than the coupon price. They have a great selection of draft beers (I had the Sam Adams Boston Lager). I would recommend this restaurant to my friends.

